@startuml cb-test-execution

title HIL Test Execution Flow - Platform Control Board

actor       "Developer"                     as Dev
participant "CB Repo\nGitHub"               as GH
participant "CB Repo CI\nGitHub Actions"    as CI
participant "Artifactory"                   as ART
participant "Raspberry Pi\nHIL Controller"  as RPi
participant "OpenOCD\nSerial Debug Probe"   as OCD
participant "MCP4922 DAC\n(SPI)"            as DAC
participant "USB-CAN FD Adapter"            as CAN
participant "Platform Control Board\n(DUT)" as DUT

== trigger ==

Dev -> GH   : git push origin develop
GH -> CI    : push event on develop via webhook
CI -> CI    : build firmware ELF (CM7)
CI -> ART   : upload ELF file with tag & commit SHA
CI -> RPi   : notify new firmware available\nArtifactory URL + commit SHA
RPi -> ART  : download ELF file
ART --> RPi : ELF file

== board fixture - setup ==

RPi -> OCD  : openocd program ELF file verify reset
OCD -> DUT  : flash ELF via SWD/JTAG
OCD --> RPi : Verified OK

RPi -> DAC  : set all zones = 75 °F ambient via SPI
RPi -> RPi  : set all interlock outputs = LOW via GPIO
RPi -> CAN  : open can0 + can1 via flush queues

RPi -> OCD  : openocd reset run
OCD -> DUT  : execute from reset vector

DUT -> CAN  : NMT heartbeat 0x701 [OPERATIONAL] via FDCAN1
CAN --> RPi : recv 0x701 via state=0x05

note over RPi : boot confirmed

== test body ==

RPi -> CAN  : can0.send() via command frame (OMS or HMI)
CAN -> DUT  : FDCAN1 Line 0/1 via command COB-ID
DUT -> CAN  : response frame via FDCAN1 Line 0/1
CAN --> RPi : can0.recv_matching(response COB-ID, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert field values

RPi -> DAC  : set zone temperature via SPI
DAC -> DUT  : analog voltage via ADC input
note over DUT : stimulus only (no CAN response)

RPi -> DUT  : assert interlock GPIO HIGH
DUT -> CAN  : output command frame via FDCAN2 Line 1
CAN --> RPi : can1.recv_matching(output COB-ID, timeout=2s)
RPi -> RPi  : assert output field values

== board fixture - teardown ==

RPi -> RPi  : release_all() = LOW via GPIO
RPi -> DAC  : close via SPI
RPi -> CAN  : close can0 + can1
RPi -> OCD  : openocd reset

RPi --> CI  : pytest-html + JUnit XML
CI -> GH    : report results via pass/fail status on commit

@enduml
